The President of the United States met with leaders from Ethiopia, Kenya, Uganda, Sudan, and the African Union to discuss South Sudan, Somalia, and regional counterterrorism issues. They discussed the negative impact of the conflict in South Sudan on the people and regional peace. They agreed that President Salva Kiir and Riek Machar must reach an agreement by August 17 under the guidance of the Intergovernmental Authority on Development (IGAD). They also emphasized the importance of cooperation on counterterrorism, supporting the African Union Mission in Somalia, and strengthening Somali governance institutions.